Sympathy Flowers







Nicholas was born on September 19, 1932 and passed away on Monday, November 14, 2016.
Nicholas was a resident of Naples, Florida at the time of passing.
HE GRADUATED LODI H.S. IN 1950. GRADUATED WITH AN ACCOUNTING DEGREE IN 1954. HE WENT ON TO FAIRLEIGH DICKENSON UNIVERSITY AND COMPLETED HIS MBA IN FINANCEACCOUNTING GRADUATING MAGNA CUM LAUDE.
HE ENTERED THE ARMY AND WAS ASSIGNED TO THE ARMY AUDIT AGENCY IN WASHINGTON D.C.
Nicholas was married to MARYANN.
A MEMORIAL MASS WILL BE CELEBRATED ON MONDAY DECEMBER 5 2016 AT 10:00 AM IN SAINT WILLIAM CATHOLIC CHURCH 601 SEAGATE DRIVE NAPLES FL.
IN LIEU OF FLOWERS DONATIONS MAY BE MADE TO CHRIST CHILD SOCIETY OF NAPLES PO BOX 770179 NAPLES 34107 OR AVOW HOSPICE 1095 WHIPPOORWILL LANE NAPLES 34105.










